+# Operational runtime plan
+
+Status: 0087 orientation and handoff.
+
+This document freezes the current development orientation before switching to a
+new conversation/context.
+
+## Current principle
+
+```text
+implementation real enough to execute
+no daemon unless unavoidable
+no service
+no OpenRC path
+no resident watcher
+no CLI for micro-modules
+importable functions first
+tests prove the path
+Scheduler loop stays stable until we have a precise handler seam
+```
+
+## What loop means
+
+The Scheduler loop is the central execution cycle:
+
+```text
+Component.tick()
+-> yield Event / Request
+-> ComponentProxy
+-> Scheduler.emit()
+-> PolicyEngine.decide()
+-> PriorityQueue
+-> Scheduler.run()
+-> Dispatcher.dispatch()
+-> Handler
+-> Request.reply
+-> ComponentProxy
+-> tick().asend(result)
+```
+
+Do not casually modify:
+
+```text
+Scheduler.run()
+PriorityQueue
+Dispatcher
+Component.tick/yield/reply contract
+```
+
+## Current implemented runtime path
+
+```text
+ControlFS desired route manifest
+-> ControlProxy prepare/sizing
+-> mmap fixed-slot route
+-> ControlFS active route state
+-> eventfd/pipe notification primitive
+-> route lease state
+-> ControlProxy pump/tick
+-> Scheduler-facing handshake
+-> Scheduler route adapter
+```
+
+Patch map:
+
+```text
+0079-r2/r3  ControlProxy prepare/sizing and bus visibility
+0080-r2     file-backed mmap fixed-slot route
+0081        active route materializer
+0082        route notification primitive using os.eventfd, ctypes eventfd or pipe fallback
+0083-r2     route lease state
+0084        ControlProxy pump/tick, no service
+0085-r2     Scheduler-facing route handshake
+0086-r2     Scheduler route adapter with authorized=True + policy_decision_id
+```
+
+## What exists now
+
+```text
+SchedulerRouteRequest authorized by policy
+-> handle_scheduler_route_request()
+-> prepare_route_for_scheduler()
+-> tick_controlproxy()
+-> active mmap route materialized
+-> lease acquired and activated
+-> SchedulerRouteReply with route_handle + lease_id
+```
+
+This is real enough to execute, but it is not yet wired into the existing
+Scheduler dispatcher.
+
+## What does not exist yet
+
+```text
+concrete Scheduler handler object
+Dispatcher registration
+real producer writing RouteMessage through route_handle
+real consumer waiting on eventfd/pipe fileno
+mmap drain into Recorder
+route generation g2/g3 for updates/resizing
+delete/drain cleanup
+inter-process locking
+VisPy adapter
+NetworkBridge
+HardwareBridge
+```
+
+## Operational priorities
+
+Next work should be more operational and less conceptual.
+
+```text
+P1 - connect a concrete Scheduler handler without changing Scheduler.run()
+P2 - create end-to-end producer write + notify + consumer drain test
+P3 - record drained RouteMessage frames into Recorder/journal
+P4 - add route generation g2 path for update/resize, no live resize
+P5 - add cleanup/drain/closed route lifecycle
+P6 - add VisPy/browser route state adapter from event.bus/context.bus
+P7 - only then evaluate inter-process locks and real /dev/shm placement
+```
+
+## Rules for the next context
+
+```text
+no daemon/service/OpenRC for ControlProxy
+no background watcher
+no CLI unless it is a true operator boundary
+module logic is importable
+tests validate behavior
+events are facts, not commands
+bus facts are not Scheduler commands
+Scheduler policy remains authority
+adapter requires authorized=True + policy_decision_id
+ControlProxy does not decide security
+mmap resize is never live; use next generation
+Qdrant remains projection/search, not source of truth
+TaskContext/ContextGate remain context authority
+```
+
+## Next patch recommendation
+
+```text
+0088 concrete Scheduler route handler
+```
+
+Why 0088 and not 0087:
+
+```text
+0087 is this operational plan and context handoff patch.
+0088 should implement the concrete handler seam.
+```
+
+Expected 0088 shape:
+
+```text
+src/runtime/scheduler_route_handler.py
+tests/test_scheduler_route_handler.py
+tests/rules/test_scheduler_route_handler_rule.py
+doc/architecture/SCHEDULER_ROUTE_HANDLER.md
+doc/changelog/0088-scheduler-route-handler.md
+```
+
+The handler should call:
+
+```text
+handle_scheduler_route_request()
+```
+
+It should not modify:
+
+```text
+Scheduler.run()
+PriorityQueue
+Dispatcher internals
+PolicyEngine
+```
+
+## First end-to-end target after 0088
+
+```text
+authorized Scheduler request
+-> Scheduler route handler
+-> Scheduler route adapter
+-> handshake
+-> pump
+-> active mmap route
+-> lease active
+-> producer writes RouteMessage frame
+-> notifier.notify(1)
+-> consumer selector sees fileno()
+-> notifier.drain()
+-> mmap route drain
+-> Recorder writes journal facts
+```
